{"product_id": "39200", "page": 1, "page_order": 3, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-02-05", "text": "The advantage of getting these games on Steam was that they would work through Steam when they might not outside of them being older games on newer systems. That is no longer true. Lately, most of these older games, that I love so much, no longer work on Steam either. That being so, what good is Steam? This is the 4th of 5th game I have recently tried to play on Steam that didn't work. I've tried uninstalling and reinstalling them to no avail. If these games are not going to work, then I no longer have any reason to bother with Steam. I even tried purchasing a couple of games because I still had money on my Steam account and they were on sale at a very good price, but they didn't work either. What good is Steam if these games just don't work on them.", "hours": 0.5, "user_id": "76561198055969475", "username": "selea", "products": 90, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 1, "page_order": 4, "recommended": false, "date": "2018-02-03", "text": "Rather than rehash all the general feedback stated by other reviewers, I'll just mention the two things that ultimately killed my enjoyment of this game. First, restarting it always puts you back in a town regardless of how much time you've spent progressiing through the game world before reaching a checkpoint. This can easily result in a half hour of tedious backtracking each time you come back to the game. Second, the game sometimes didn't save my mission progress even when I manually saved multiple times during a session, resulting in more tedious repetition of conversations, buying and selling, inventory management, routine combat, etc. (this also led to wasted time searching through forum posts for help with the problem).\nOK, I'll also mention that the camera and basic movement mechanics are badly implemented and frustrating. Very disappointing.", "hours": 24.4, "user_id": "76561198011272407", "username": "rwnospam", "products": 29, "early_access": false}
