{"product_id": "39200", "page": 5, "page_order": 9, "recommended": false, "date": "2017-09-29", "text": "OK, here I go.\nTo be honest I really want to recommend this game.\nI know how amazing it is, BUT the steam version is a hot piece of garbage.\nIt really is.\nMost of the user guides (except for one) are on how to solve problems with this game, make it actually playable and make it not look like utter trash.\nSo if and when you buy this, know that you first have to do some things in order to get this working.\npeople are also struggeling with getting multiplayer mode to work (keep that in mind if that's important to you).\nHonestly the game is great, a good story nice characters (and a lot of them), a way better character design screen than in the first dungeon siege, more spells, puzzles, variety in world design and environments, nice dungeons, a lot of pets, skilltrees that don't suck (so it's actually nice to play as a warior or archer), a small tutorial done right, passive magic that makes companions actually useable, a lot of ways to tackle character builds and team compostion, pretty nice graphics ....\nA lot of good things are in this game, but\nit's a touble getting it working, I actually had to buy another steam program which cost me more than this game in order to get this game to work in fullscreen. (I highly recommend checking the guides)\nThe AI is still\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 but less likely to just kill itself than in the first game (however more likely to just not engage at all.\nhad to pay \u20ac3,99 for borderless gaming, which is just stupid and shouldn't be neccesary.\nall in all a way rougher experience than the first itteration, if you want a game that's playable from the getgo than go for dungeon siege 1.\nAll in all I wouldn't really want to recommend it because it should just work in my opinion, but it's a great game nonetheless.\nIf you want to buy it just be aware of this versions downfalls, maybe get it on\nor something", 