{"product_id": "39200", "page": 23, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-12-30", "text": "Still fun, 10 years after my first playthrough... Surprisingly modern feeling for a 10 year old game. Can be played casually, but allows for more advanced things like kiting, orb walking, animation cancelling. Items are complex enough to add depth and a good level of \"spreadsheeting\" (crunching numbers to identify the best gear combo's etc...), and the skill systems are pleasant and rewarding.\nSome classes do out-shine others (archer seems to be the strongest in Vanilla by far) but due to the game not being too difficult, you are not forced to play with the strongest - just play with whatever you want.\nOverall , still a great game even now. Would be nice to see a modern version - There are other dungeon crawlers out there at the moment (Diablo 3 is great) but not quite play like DSII. But for the price, I would not hesitate to recommend this.", "hours": 55.3, "username": "a e s t h e t i c", "products": 81, "early_access": false}
