{"product_id": "39200", "page": 25, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-10-04", "text": "So this game is somewhat repetitive. But it's still fun as long as breaks are taken occiasionally.\nI've got a friend who says this is his favorite RPG ever. I can't see why. This is by no means a bad game but there are better ones. If you've played Torchlight a dozen times, crushed all the orcs in Lord of the Rings Online, and slain the ultimate boss in FATE then this game will give you something new.\nThere is no 1 town you go to. No shopkeeps you keep going back to. No place you will call home for more than couple hours of gameplay. This game has you travel through countless areas as you progress down the storyline. From a dense jungle, to a barren desert, to misty mountain roads, to woodlands infested with all sorts of monsters.\nPros-\n-Don't stick in 1 place long enough to get bored with it\n-Loads of varied inviroments\n-A party system. And a fairly good one at that\n-Good story\n-Variety in everything from weapons to monsters to shopkeeps and towns\nCons-\n-Can be repetitive\n-Boring to play for hours on end\n-You have to play through the game multiple times to get a full party. You start with 4 and can get up to 6 by completing the game twice\n-Graphics have aged horribly. Like really badly. All the characters and mobs are super chunky. As is the enviroment.", "hours": 17.2, "username": "Overlord Neb", "products": 160, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 25, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2015-09-27", "text": "This game is so different from DS1, but somehow still the same. Is that even possible? The monster-slaying, axe-wielding, quest-completing epic fantasy says so.\npicking up on that \"epic\"... Dungeon Siege is probably one of the very, very,\nfew games to make me feel like an\nhero, not some \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 mercenary who just happens to be the world's saviour.", "hours": 7.2, "user_id": "76561198187330631", "username": "Trident", "products": 44, "early_access": false}
