{"product_id": "39200", "page": 37, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-07-20", "text": "Absolutely Love this old timer, but to my dissapointment- I played for 12 hours yesterday saved my game 2 times (I always do to be sure that way) exited out of the game to the game start menu. woke up the next morning and hit the contue button only to have it put me 15 lvls lower and way back near the starting point.\nI still love the game but it seems after all the cleaning out files reloading backup saves and every other troubleshooting option that it will not let me save any further.........Oh how dissapointing!!!!!", "hours": 87.5, "user_id": "76561198076194542", "username": "dabbott73", "products": 11, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 37, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-07-14", "text": "One of the most memorable games from my younger years. Both DS1 and 2 were great games, and are still great to play today. The only reason I'm giving this a negative review is the fact that multiplayer is just simply disabled. I'm not sure if it's because of a GameSpy thing, or because Steam just doesn't want to support multiplayer servers, regardless either way I'm disappointed. While this game is definitely still enjoyable single player, it really shined in the multiplayer. The lack of DLC (expansion) that already exists for the game doesn't help either.\nIf you don't mind playing single player then this game is still worth buying. Also Steam, good on you for not listing ANYWHERE on the store page that multiplayer is disabled (sarcasm if you couldn't tell). I bought this with the full expectation that I would be able to play co-op.", "hours": 15.9, "username": "~DEV!OUS~", "products": 263, "early_access": false}
