{"product_id": "39200", "page": 39, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-25", "text": "Dungeon Siege 2 keeps the same format as DS1, with a few improvements. Now there is a single player replayability target. In order to really complete the game, it is necessary to finish it at least 3 times using the same character, due to the XP level suggested for each difficulty level.\nNow it is possible to craft special items, instead of waiting for them to appear as loot, there are special powers that can be used sometimes during battles. The inventory part suffered some small changes, but keeps almost the same as the first game. The main change in character development is that now it is possible to improve some type of ability as you level up.\nFor fans of the first game it is as good as that one. unfortunately, as DS1, DS2 steam version does not include the Broken World expansion, but even like this there will be many hours of play time.", "hours": 2.9, "username": "gfs555", "products": 1067, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 39, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-24", "text": "Steam Forced me to play Non-Steam Version because steam doesnt have datadisk \"Broken World\" which is pretty important + with non steam version i can play with friends.Steam version only offline.Not cool man not cool", "hours": 63.2, "username": "Broseidon", "products": 228, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 39, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-05-21", "text": "Where to start.... This game is amazing! Might be old, but it's the game that sparked my love for RPG's. The replayability is amazing, with different classes and races to choose from. The gameplay is extremely good. Only downfall is the graphics, but what would you expect from a game this old. It is still one of the best RPG games ever!", "hours": 107.5, "user_id": "76561198032726450", "username": "Creed", "products": 89, "early_access": false}
