{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-02-01", "text": "One of my favourite games of all time. The graphics are a bit outdated, but the amazing gameplay makes up for that. The story is a bit clich\u00e9 and the game gets repetitive at times. But it's still my personal favourite RPG of the century. If you wish to try this game i would definitley recommend it.\nWarning: no expansion and no multiplayer\n8.5/10 great game", "hours": 0.6, "user_id": "76561198041280794", "username": "Schoenlepel", "products": 52, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 2, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-27", "text": "I like lots of things about DS2.  I like that item shops are useful, that they tried to give your companions actual characters, and that the female models wear sensible armor.  I liked the design of several boss fights, and the efforts they went to (in some areas, anyway) to disguise the basic linearity of the game.\nUnfortunately, DS2 is one of those games where you had to buy the DLC to get the actual ending - DLC that doesn't seem to be on Steam.  So this game gets to the climax and goes \"HAHANOPE\".  Completely unsatisfying.", "hours": 44.1, "username": "crowroadaw", "products": 649, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-23", "text": "A game of my childhood. It's like one of those games you would just kill time on. Even if the graphics are not modern - the game is a classic and this game is one of the best RPG adventures. It would really suit some achievements for this game too, but I guess classic... stays classic.", "hours": 15.5, "username": "Lukas #YouTubeGaming", "products": 804, "early_access": false}
