{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-22", "text": "A beautifully crafted RPG, which removes the only problem Dungeon Siege 1 had by adding in an ability system that added bonuses to the player's characters as they kept going. At the same time, this means that it's not as easy to automate, but it still provides a fun and immersive experience which I enjoyed to its fullest.", "hours": 84.8, "user_id": "76561198023366877", "username": "Newt", "products": 346, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-22", "text": "The strongest game in the Dungeon Seige series that can be played alone since the series is rather loosely connected. In my opinion the other games are not quite as good though they have individual strengths.\nDS2 has an evil Prince that steals a powerful artifact to become as per usual a God,  and your job, along with your party members is to geld the upstart! The game has a lot of gameplay substance even if it is by 2014 somewhat generic in nature. The story is rather shallow as well but what can be expected...this isn't even vaguely on the level of say...one of the Malazan Book of the Fallen novels (Steve please encourage someone to do a Malazan game..Memories of Ice would be a great one to do!).\nI think for its price DS2 is pretty decent in its capacity to entertain and I would recommend it. Just don't expect too much though it is a good timekiller, generates a few laughs, and de-stresses as you mow down enemies galore!", "hours": 63.9, "user_id": "76561198034927328", "username": "jpbowman", "products": 34, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 7, "recommended": false, "date": "2014-01-21", "text": "I spent many hours playing this with multiple character builds before I got it on steam, lots of fun had. I bought the Dungeon Siege bundle x3 on steam expecting ease of use, functionality and no drama in getting it to work and sorting out CD keys and updates on multiple computers of my family...\nStarted game\nMultiplayer disabled\nNot cool.\nI normally would give this a big thumbs up but the steam version has multiplayer disabled because the online servers are no longer in existence, the problem is that local/LAN has also been disabled along with that for no reason at all other than laziness I guess, because they just disabled the multiplayer menu button in the main menu.\nEven when I played this by myself I used the multiplayer function so that I could use my characters when I wanted to play with friends and for certain features in the game host settings that were not in singleplayer.\nSo you are better off getting it somewhere else.", "hours": 0.4, "user_id": "76561197979969103", "username": "Kiros", "products": 253, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-15", "text": "One of my favorite games of all times!!!! Great gameplay and varibilty in character development creates alot of replay ability!!", "hours": 39.7, "username": "Ligerten", "products": 385, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 41, "page_order": 9, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-08", "text": "It's hard to express just how much fun I had with this game. Really refined from the first entry in the series, and adds a lot of depth to character development. Managing a party instead of just one character allows you to experiement with several builds at once, and you'll unlock larger parties at higher difficulty levels. The structure of quests and sidequests often have you exploring areas you couldn't access earlier in the game, giving some good variety in where you'll be going and why.\nOverall a very worthy dungeon crawler standing toe-to-toe with DIablo 2 or Titan Quest", "hours": 79.0, "username": "Action Jay", "products": 595, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 42, "page_order": 0, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-03", "text": "Simply loved playing through the entire game !  Multiple members in your party, lots of questing to do, plenty of places to explore, challenging levels, awesome game !", "hours": 88.6, "user_id": "76561197974331580", "username": "McClane", "products": 208, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 42, "page_order": 1, "recommended": true, "date": "2014-01-01", "text": "Wow this game is awesome. I've been playing games for 25+ years and this is one of my favorites. The stats on weapon drops from the drops is fun to compare, the fights are fun, you can pause the game to switch party members and switch weapons/spells/etc. by pushing the space bar which is really fun for strategizing, the game doesn't feel linear because you can explore out a bit and there are side quests. The story is nice. The cities are cool. There is an elf city which has a lift to get up which is pretty cool as well; really enjoying this one. I'd give this 9/10. The graphics are still decent, but it's the gameplay that makes this one shine.\nIf your trying to pick one Dungeon Siege game I'd go with 2, followed by the first one, and then the Dungeon Siege III.", "hours": 22.0, "user_id": "76561198002189495", "username": "rovaira2", "products": 181, "early_access": false}
