{"product_id": "39200", "page": 46, "page_order": 2, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-11-25", "text": "Talent trees? Check. Efficient game design? Check. Fun weaponry and cool abilities from unlocked talents? Check. Certainly repetitive as any Dungeon Crawling game is, Dungeon Siege II at least has the decency to not try to pretend it isn't what it is, and it gives you full freedom to do whatever the \u2665\u2665\u2665\u2665 it is you want. Overall a step up from the first.\n9/10", "hours": 0.3, "username": "Kaldaris", "products": 330, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 46, "page_order": 3, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-08-12", "text": "This is the DS 2.  Not many people know about it because it wasn't very popular at the time.  It was quickly overshadowed by other, more well-known handheld systems such as the Playstation Portable, the Atari Lynx, the Sega Dreamcast, a fluffy kitten, and the Nintoaster.  I recommend getting the physical DS 2 instead of the download one, because the screen on my download one keeps falling off, and I have to re-download new ones.", "username": "Dire Miralis", "products": 318, "early_access": false}
