{"product_id": "39200", "page": 46, "page_order": 5, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-07-08", "text": "Very different from DS1. In Dungeon Siege 2 (as in Diablo 2. Hmm...) there are character classes, and linear levelling. Humbug.\nGood story, good controls, fun characters. I seem to recall not worrying terribly about my equipment, but it's been a while. I remember the game being very easy to play, and the levelling system being largely responsible. I also remember the bosses being terribly easy once you figure out each one's trick.\nNot a bad game, but not really anyithing special either.\nB-", "username": "thorvindr", "products": 410, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 46, "page_order": 6, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-06-08", "text": "Dungeon Siege II features more of the action and party mechanics that made the first Dungeon Siege a hit, but with better graphics and story.\nStill, it all feels a bit old by today's standards. It's unlikely that this game will now appeal to any but those seeking a nostalgia kick for 2005.", "hours": 2.1, "username": "7grain", "products": 355, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 46, "page_order": 7, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-05-12", "text": "Die gelungene Fortsetzung eines genialen Spiels. Die Story ist nicht schlecht, wenn auch am Ende etwas zu offen. Ansonsten ist das Spiel eigentlich genau so wie der Vorg\u00e4nger. Im generellen Spielprinzip und im Kampfsystem gibt es keine gr\u00f6\u00dferen \u00c4nderungen, so das sich Fan\u00b4s des ersten Spiels ganz schnell reinfinden. Etwas Schade ist, das die wenigen Filme die es gibt noch nicht einmal \u00fcbersetzt wurden. Ansonsten kann Dungeon Siege II aber getrost als sehr gelungen bezeichnet werden.", "hours": 68.2, "user_id": "76561198039137828", "username": "Sotar89", "products": 244, "early_access": false}
{"product_id": "39200", "page": 46, "page_order": 8, "recommended": true, "date": "2012-04-01", "text": "Previous review sucked soo. This game was a game I bought when I lost my key to Sacred and had to reformat my computer years ago. This game is an amazing party based dungeon crawler. You have four different skill paths to go down (Combat magic, nature magic, melee, ranged). Within this paths are many different paths to help create a unique party. You should have one from each class and specialize in that class or you will end up being weak. The story on this game is amazing for the most part (starting area sucks). If you want a Diablo 2 ish game with an amazing party system then play this. This one is five times better than Dungeon Siege 3!", "hours": 6.9, "username": "Zai", "products": 1183, "early_access": false}
